The latest blow to De Lille comes from a Gauteng businessman who has accused her of trying to solicit a multi-million rand bribed from him six years ago. CAPE TOWN - Cape Town Mayor Patricia de Lille has strongly denied claims of corruption leveled against by the Demcratic Alliance (DA). The latest blow to De Lille comes from a Gauteng businessman who has accused her of trying to solicit a multi-million rand bribed from him six years ago. The DA has now laid a criminal complaint against the mayor. De Lille has scoffed at the claims. "There is a serious attempt to damage my reputation and the haste to get rid of me is reaching desperate heights. People have become blind in their anger or hate for me." De Lille is at war with the DA's city caucus on various fronts. The party has also brought a motion of no confidence against her.